          "body": "The chapter culminates in a cry: *Wretched man that I am! Who will set me free from the body of this death?* (v. 24). The cry is not despair; it is the precondition of deliverance. Until the soul has stopped hoping in its own will and Law-effort, it cannot receive what only the risen Christ and the Spirit can give. The doxology answers immediately: *Thanks be to God through Jesus Christ our Lord!* (v. 25). But Paul does not yet resolve the tension. The final summary holds both terms: with the mind I serve God's Law; with the flesh, the law of sin. Romans 7 stops here — leaving the reader poised on the edge of 8:1: *Therefore there is now no condemnation for those who are in Christ Jesus*. The chapter ends not with resolution but with rescue named; chapter 8 will unfold the rescue's mechanism."
